 Mental models<body>  Mental models    Mental models are representations   of the function and/or structure of objects in peoples' minds.      may be incorrect or incomplete      can be "executed"      are analogical representations,     or a combination of analogical and propositional representations      are dynamically constructed     when required        Two main types:     Functional models (good     for everyday use)      Structural models (good     for breakdown situations; difficult to acquire from usage experience only)                 Computer        systems should be designed in such a way that users can quickly acquire        a good        functional model of the system (that is also in accordance with their        task model).          </body> 